  "activities": [
    ["1", "2", "3", "4", "5"],
    [
      "<b>Part 1: Introduction to Descriptions</b>:<br><br>Describing is providing details or explaining what something is like, such as describing an experience or an event you have attended.<br><br>Experience: This refers to something you have done or lived through, like a holiday or a fun day out.<br><br>Event: This is something that happens, such as a party, concert, or school activity.<br><br>Arrangements: These are plans that you make with others, like organizing a meet-up with friends or scheduling an appointment.<br><br>Intentions: These are your future plans, such as 'I am going to study' or 'I will visit my grandparents.'",
      "<b>Part 2: Describing Experiences</b>:<br><br>When describing an experience, use specific details to make the experience clear to others. For example, instead of just saying, 'I had a good holiday,' you could say, 'I had a wonderful holiday at the beach where I swam in the sea, built sandcastles, and ate ice cream every day.'<br><br>Describing experiences helps the listener imagine what it was like, just like telling a story.<br><br>Example Sentences:<br>'Last weekend, I went to a concert. It was loud and exciting, and I danced the whole time!'<br>'I went to the zoo and saw lions, elephants, and monkeys. I loved the elephant show!'",
      "<b>Part 3: Reporting Events, Arrangements, and Intentions</b>:<br><br>Reporting Events: This involves telling someone about an event that has happened. Use the past tense to describe it.<br><br>Example: 'The school play was last night. It was amazing, and the audience loved the performance!'<br><br>Making Arrangements: When making arrangements, you inform others about plans and confirm details.<br><br>Example: 'I am meeting my friend at the park at 4 PM tomorrow.'<br><br>Describing Intentions: When you talk about your intentions, you explain what you plan to do.<br><br>Example: 'I intend to study for my math test this weekend.'",
      "<b>Part 4: Putting It All Together</b>:<br><br>Describing experiences, reporting events, and discussing arrangements or intentions are important for sharing what happens in your life or what you plan to do.<br><br>Using words and phrases like 'I went to,' 'I plan to,' 'I’m going to,' and 'It was' will help you create clear reports and descriptions.",
      "<b>Part 5: Exercise (Practice Time)</b>:<br><br><b>Exercise 1: Describing Experiences</b><br>Think about a memorable experience you had recently (e.g., a holiday, a party, a school trip). Write at least 4 sentences describing it in detail.<br><br><b>Exercise 2: Reporting an Event</b><br>Write 3 sentences about an event that you have attended (e.g., a concert, a birthday party, a sports match). Use the past tense.<br><br><b>Exercise 3: Making Arrangements</b><br>Write a dialogue between you and a friend where you are making arrangements to meet. Include details like time, place, and activity.<br><br><b>Exercise 4: Describing Intentions</b><br>Write 3 sentences describing your intentions for the weekend or the upcoming holidays. Use future tense ('I will,' 'I plan to,' 'I am going to')."
    ]
  ],
